  "text": "What a night in the World Cup! Round of 16, 7 July 2026, Vancouver — and Switzerland outlasted Colombia across a goalless night and won the shootout to reach their first quarter-final since 1954. Seventy-two years of hurt sat on Swiss shoulders; ninety minutes, extra time and twelve yards would decide whether it finally lifted.\n\nNinety minutes, extra time — and still nothing could separate them. Goalless, but never, ever dull.\n\nNeither side could find a way through in ninety minutes or extra time; chances came and went at both ends without reward. The shootout brought the drama the open play had withheld. Davinson Sánchez rattled his spot-kick against the bar and Gregor Kobel saved smartly from Cucho Hernández, before Rubén Vargas held his nerve to send Switzerland through 4-3. For a nation that had waited generations, this was catharsis — and a quarter-final date with the champions to come.\n\nYou could feel the tension crackle around the ground with every attack.\n\nThis is knockout football at its rawest — win, or fly home.\n\nThe neutrals were on their feet; nobody in the building sat still.\n\nFULL-TIME: Switzerland 0–0 Colombia! Switzerland march on, Colombia head home heartbroken — and here's the beautiful part: every goal, every minute you just heard is locked on-chain and verified by TxLINE. No hot air, no guesswork, just receipts. What. A. Game!",
